column168: FREIGHT BROUGHT TO FT/DFW DOCK BY LAND AIR TRUCKING FOR OUR ACCEPTANCE AND MOVEMENT TO SCOTLAND. THE DANGEROUS GOODS INSPECTOR RECEIVING THE FREIGHT N OTED THAT THERE WERE SOME SEVERE DENTS AND THAT THERE WERE SOME TEARS IN TH E METAL OF THE DRUM. HE IMMEDIATELY NOTIFIED HIS DUTY SUPERVISOR WHO IN TUR N NOTIFIED THE FT/DFW DANGEROUS GOODS COORDINATOR. THE FREIGHT WAS SEGREGAT ED FROM OTHER TRAFFIC AND PLACED AWAY FROM POPULATED AREAS. ALL GOVERNMENT AGENCIES WERE NOTIFIED (FAA, DOT, NRC, DOE, TEXAS DEPT OF HEALTH) AS WELL A S THE LOCAL FIRE DEPARTMENT AND AIRPORT OPERATIONS. AFTER EMERGENCY AGENCIE S WERE NOTIFIED, LOCAL DFW TERMINAL MANAGER AND OUR HDQ OPERATIONS CONTROL WERE CALLED. IN THE ADDITION TO THE ABOVE, WESTERN EMERGENCY SERVICES WAS N OTIFIED TO BRING A DOT 17 E DRUM TO THE TERMINAL AND TO RENDER ASSISTANCE A S NECESSARY. AFTER INSPECTION AND RELEASE BY ABOVE LISTED AGENCIES, THE FRE IGHT WAS PLACED IN THE RE-COOPING DRUM AND THE SHIPPER WAS NOTIFIED TO RE-C LAIM HIS FREIGHT.  DAMAGE: DENTS AND TEARS IN THE METAL FABRIC OF THE DRUM CAUSE:  APPARENT FORKLIFT BLADE PUNCTURES. PER VERBAL CONVERSATION WITH LAN D AIR TRUCKING, THEIR DRIVER INDICATED THAT PRIOR TO HIS DROPPING THE RADIO ACTIVE FREIGHT AT FT, HE HAD TAKEN FREIGHT OVER TO AMERICAN AIRLINES. HE SA ID THAT WHILE PICKING UP A SKID OF THEIR FREIGHT, AN AMERICAN EMPLOYEE PUNC TURED AND DENTED THE CAN OF CS-137 WITH HIS FORKLIFT.
